(In reply to Mark Millard from comment #9)

The only lines that are different in the U-Boot fdt print outputs
(and the prior "DRAM:" output for context) are 4 pairs of them:

DRAM:  948 MiB (effective 1.9 GiB)
vs.
DRAM:  948 MiB (effective 7.9 GiB)

The rng-seed = . . . pair of lines (not shown here)

Later:

        scb {
. . .
                pcie@7d500000 {

had:

                        dma-ranges = <0x02000000 0x00000004 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x7be00000>;
vs.
                        dma-ranges = <0x02000000 0x00000004 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000002 0x00000000>;

And even later:

        memory@0 {
                device_type = "memory";

had:

                reg = <0x00000000 0x00000000 0x3b400000 0x00000000 0x40000000 0x3be00000>;
vs.
                reg = <0x00000000 0x00000000 0x3b400000 0x00000000 0x40000000 0xbc000000 0x00000001 0x00000000 0x80000000 0x00000001 0x80000000 0x80000000>;

That is it for fdt print output differences as seen via U-Boot.
